text: Monognathus ahlstromi, the paddletail onejaw, is an ocean-dwelling eel found in the North Pacific Ocean off of the coast of the United States. It is found up to a depth of 2,000 m.Catalog of Fishes search. Research.calacademy.org. Retrieved on 2012-07-27.Fishbase.org Retrieved March 10, 2010 It does not provide parental care. Little information is currently known about its habits or full distribution. ==Description== The dorsal and anal fins of Monognathus ahlstromi lack bony supports.Monognathus ahlstromi (Paddletail onejaw).
